reviews.review_text: Very good recording  Hot, fun show. Excellent NFA>Black Peter.

best recording? This show is magnficent.  Who could argue with a 1st set ending Bird Song, CC Rider, Althea, Let It Grow > Franklin's Tower?  This is the only pairing of the last two besides Seattle 9/29/77.  The second set ups the ante with Terrapin > Playin > He's Gone -- probably the best Playin of the year, and definitely a keeper.  There's an extra jam at the end of NFA -- doesn't it have a name?

A fairly rapid comparison suggested this is the best sounding recording, but second opinions are always a help.
